summary: Trying to figure out which version of Spider-Man is the best version is a bit of a pointless debate. If all the versions of...
body: Trying to figure out which version of Spider-Man is the best version is a bit of a pointless debate. If all the versions of Spider-Man met, they would go into an existential crisis and convince each other that they’re not the best Spider-Man. Some of them might even apologize for making it so difficult. With that said, if all the other Spideys can’t decide who’s the best, how do you expect me to know?

summary: The absence of Tony in the Far From Home trailer freaked me out but does anyone else think it’s a little weird that Marvel’s...
body: The absence of Tony in the Far From Home trailer freaked me out but does anyone else think it’s a little weird that Marvel’s crushing our hopes now? They’re basically spoiling the events of Endgame by giving us all this evidence that makes the possibility of Tony dying seem almost certain. This might be wishful thinking, but what if Tony isn’t dead? Maybe he’s in a coma or missing or something. Marvel knows how much time we spend analysing these trailers, so I doubt they’d spoil what may be the biggest movie of 2019 with a Spider-Man trailer. Anyways, thanks for coming to my Ted Talk.

Just wanna let you know:

Just because someone doesn’t ship PeterxMichelle doesn’t mean they are racist or anything. There’s a thing called ‘chemistry’ or 'development’ and some people just don’t see it between them WHICH IS OK.

There are many reason to not ship people and there’s no need to hate on those who don’t or on those who do or on anyone else (excluding the people who ship pedophilia/incest bc that’s just wrong don’t @ me).
